
Overview of verb hover

The verb hover has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) hover, vibrate, vacillate, oscillate -- (be undecided about something; waver between conflicting positions or courses of action; "He oscillates between accepting the new position and retirement")
2. (2) hover, linger -- (move to and fro; "The shy student lingered in the corner")
3. (2) hover -- (hang in the air; fly or be suspended above)
4. (1) levitate, hover -- (be suspended in the air, as if in defiance of gravity; "The guru claimed that he could levitate")
5. brood, hover, loom, bulk large -- (hang over, as of something threatening, dark, or menacing; "The terrible vision brooded over her all day long")
